(204, 'BusinessEnquiry', 'BusinessEditCoal', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Hi,\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nOn behalf of the International Forum for Environment, Sustainability and Technology (iFOREST), I am writing to request time from a senior stakeholder for a short interview on the issue of clean energy transition and just transition in India.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nThe requested interview is in relation to our ongoing research on understanding the opinion of various stakeholders on coal phase down and just transition, and the challenges and opportunities of it.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nWe request you time for the interview anytime by June 17 (even a weekend time is fine), as per your convenience and availability. We can do the meeting through an online platform (zoom or google meet), and also through telephonic means.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nThe interview will be specifically focussing on the following aspects:\r\n\r\na.       Perspective on clean energy transition, and phasing down of coal mining activities in the coming decades.\r\n\r\nb.      Possible impacts of coal mine closure at the national and sub-national level.\r\n\r\nc.       Observations/opinions from any previous experiences on impacts of mine closure on local and regional level (such as cases of previous mine closures, cases of socio-economic challenges triggered by it, and other coal-dependent industries, etc.).\r\n\r\nd.      Opinion on measures that may be adopted to ensure a planned phased-down, minimize any disruptions, and ensure overall positive environmental, social, and economic outcomes.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nBy way of introduction, iFOREST is a New Delhi based environmental research and innovation organization. The mission of iFOREST is to develop, support and mainstream policies, strategies, technologies and solutions that are environmentally sound and socially inclusive. Our team has more than a decade’s experience of understanding the challenges of mining-affected areas and addressing them. One of our flagship initiatives is Climate Change and Just Transition. We have also developed the India Just Transition Centre (IJTC) to work on the issue of environmentally sustainable, economically viable and socially inclusive low-carbon transition in the face of the growing challenges of climate change. We have an eminent advisory board to guide our work on transition, including Shri Jairam Ramesh ji, Chairperson, Parliamentary Standing Committee on Science and Technology, Environment, Forests and Climate Change.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nOnce we receive confirmation from your end on the date and timing, we can also share a set of 5-6 questions for the interview.\r\n\r\nWe sincerely look forward to your time and support.\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\n\r\nPreet Kumar\r\nManager, Just Transition\r\nEmail: preet@iforest.global | Cell: +91 7604046601\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Preet Kumar', 'preet@iforest.global', '7604046601', 'General Enquiry', NULL, NULL, 'Active'),
